author: 13abc
title: Reopening of I-75 bridge delayed
text:
U.S. 6 between State Route 25 and done bridge road was still closed after 6:00 a.m. Monday.
ODOT slid a bridge for southbound I-75 in place over the weekend.
This is the first time this was done in Ohio.
ODOT says shims under the rollers allowing the bridge to move were stuck under those rollers.
It says the shims are out, crews can place the actual bearings that the bridge sits on to allow traffic to go over it.
ODOT said this project was the only issue during the slide.
ODOT plans to do the same thing on the northbound side next month.
